---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Merit — Open Source Cold Outreach Intelligence · 701am"
  description="Merit is an open source cold outreach intelligence framework. Research-led. Humanized. Built for agencies running campaigns across multiple clients — without the copy-paste, without the generic openers."
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
    { name: 'Merit' },
  ]}
>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════
       HERO
       ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <header class="mt-hero">
    <div class="mt-hero-inner">
      <p class="mt-hero-eyebrow">
        <span class="mt-hero-rule"></span>
        Open Source · MIT License · Built for agencies
        <span class="mt-hero-rule"></span>
      </p>
      <h1 class="mt-hero-h">
        Your clients are paying for outreach.<br />
        <em>Their prospects can tell.</em>
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-hero-deck">
        Merit is an open source cold outreach intelligence framework. Research-led. Humanized. Built for agencies running campaigns across multiple clients — without the copy-paste, without the generic openers, without the messages that read like they came from a tool.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-hero-ctas">
        <a class="btn-primary" href="https://github.com/701am/Merit">
          Clone on GitHub — Free
          <span class="btn-icon" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>
        <a class="btn-link" href="#how-it-works">
          See how it works
          <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">↓</span>
        </a>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-hero-footnote">
        MIT License · No subscription · No per-seat fees · Runs locally
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════
       THE QUOTE
       ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="mt-section mt-section--quote">
    <div class="mt-quote">
      <div class="mt-quote-rule"></div>
      <p class="mt-quote-text">
        “The prospect deletes before the second line. The reply never comes. The offer never lands. <em>Merit exists for the agencies that refuse to accept that.</em>”
      </p>
      <div class="mt-quote-rule"></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════
       THE PROBLEM
       ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="mt-section mt-section--warm">
    <div class="section-label">
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
      <div class="label-text">§ 01 — Why agency outreach fails</div>
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-problem-intro">
      <h2 class="mt-problem-h">
        You're sending volume.<br />
        <em>They're reading noise.</em>
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-problem-lede">
        The inbox your client's prospect wakes up to has forty messages in it. Thirty-eight of them start with "I hope this finds you well." Two of them mention something real. Those two get replies.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-problem-lede">
        Agency outreach fails for three reasons — and none of them are the client's offer.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-problems">
      <article class="mt-problem">
        <p class="mt-problem-num">01</p>
        <div class="mt-problem-body">
          <h3 class="mt-problem-h3">One message. Every client.</h3>
          <p>The same sequence structure, the same angle, the same opener cadence — ported from client to client with the logos swapped. It's efficient. It's also the reason reply rates plateau at 3% and stay there. The message isn't wrong. It's just indistinguishable from every other message the prospect received today.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="mt-problem">
        <p class="mt-problem-num">02</p>
        <div class="mt-problem-body">
          <h3 class="mt-problem-h3">Personalization as decoration.</h3>
          <p>"Hi [First Name], I noticed [Company] recently [trigger event]." That's not personalization. That's a mail merge with ambition. Real personalization means the first line of the email could only have been written for this person, after someone actually looked at what they've been saying and doing. Agencies don't have time to do that manually. So they don't. And it shows.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="mt-problem">
        <p class="mt-problem-num">03</p>
        <div class="mt-problem-body">
          <h3 class="mt-problem-h3">AI copy that reads like AI copy.</h3>
          <p>The rhythm is too consistent. The transitions are too clean. The CTA sounds like it was drafted in a tool — because it was. Sophisticated buyers, which is exactly who agencies are usually targeting, recognize it immediately. The trust is gone before the second sentence.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="mt-problem">
        <p class="mt-problem-num">04</p>
        <div class="mt-problem-body">
          <h3 class="mt-problem-h3">No memory between clients.</h3>
          <p>Every new client campaign starts from a blank page. The ICP gets rebuilt. The angles get brainstormed again. The voice gets guessed at. There's no system carrying institutional knowledge forward — which means every campaign pays the same ramp-up cost, over and over.</p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════
       THE SOLUTION
       ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="mt-section">
    <div class="section-label">
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
      <div class="label-text">§ 02 — The framework</div>
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-solution">
      <h2 class="mt-solution-h">
        Merit doesn't fix the message.<br />
        <em>It fixes the system that produces the message.</em>
      </h2>

      <div class="mt-solution-body">
        <p>Merit is a cold outreach intelligence framework that runs inside Claude Code or OpenCode. It's not a SaaS. Not a tool. Not a dashboard. It's a set of files — skills and memory — that your agency installs once, fills in per client, and runs locally. Permanently.</p>
        <p>For each client, Merit maintains a complete operating context: who they are, what they're selling, how they speak, who they're targeting, what's working, and what's dead. Every message is written from that context. Nothing is templated. Nothing is generic. Nothing could have been sent by a different agency for a different client.</p>
        <p>The result is outreach that reads like the founder wrote it at 11pm because they genuinely believe this is right for the person on the other end. <em>Because the system made it that way.</em></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════
       THE CHAIN — How it works
       ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="mt-section mt-section--warm" id="how-it-works">
    <div class="section-label">
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
      <div class="label-text">§ 03 — How Merit works</div>
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-chain">
      <h2 class="mt-chain-h">
        Three stages.<br />
        <em>Every message. Always.</em>
      </h2>

      <div class="mt-chain-grid">
        <article class="mt-link">
          <div class="mt-link-head">
            <p class="mt-link-num">STEP 01</p>
            <h3 class="mt-link-h">The <em>Researcher</em></h3>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-link-p">Before a word is written, Merit researches the prospect. LinkedIn activity, company signals, recent posts, funding announcements, job postings, competitive moves. It maps trigger events — the specific moments that create urgency — and ranks them by recency and relevance. The output is a Research Dossier stored per contact, confidence-rated <strong>HIGH / MEDIUM / LOW</strong>, refreshed automatically when stale. No message starts without one.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="mt-link">
          <div class="mt-link-head">
            <p class="mt-link-num">STEP 02</p>
            <h3 class="mt-link-h">The <em>Skill</em></h3>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-link-p"><strong>cold-email</strong>, <strong>cold-dm</strong>, <strong>followup</strong>, <strong>personalization</strong>, <strong>sequence-builder</strong> — every output skill reads the dossier before writing. The first line comes from a real trigger event. The proof maps to their industry. The CTA is calibrated to their channel and communication style. The system is architecturally incapable of producing a generic message because it will not write without source material.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="mt-link">
          <div class="mt-link-head">
            <p class="mt-link-num">STEP 03</p>
            <h3 class="mt-link-h">The <em>Humanizer</em></h3>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-link-p">The final pass on every message. Ten-point rewrite: sentence rhythm varied, metronomic patterns broken, hedge words removed, passive voice made active, transitions cut, CTA shortened until it feels typed not composed, research details rewritten until they feel discovered not inserted. It doesn't change meaning. <em>It removes every tell that a tool was involved.</em></p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════
       WHAT'S INSIDE — 12 skills
       ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="mt-section">
    <div class="section-label">
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
      <div class="label-text">§ 04 — What's inside</div>
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-inside">
      <h2 class="mt-inside-h">
        12 skills. One system.<br />
        <em>A complete outreach operation in a folder.</em>
      </h2>

      <div class="mt-inside-chain">
        <h3 class="mt-inside-subhead">The Chain — runs on every message</h3>
        <div class="mt-inside-grid">
          <div class="mt-inside-card">
            <p class="mt-inside-card-label">The Researcher</p>
            <p class="mt-inside-card-p">Four-layer prospect intelligence. The person, the company, trigger events, angle match. Stored per contact. Confidence-rated. Refreshes at 60 days.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-inside-card">
            <p class="mt-inside-card-label">The Skill</p>
            <p class="mt-inside-card-p"><strong>cold-email</strong> · <strong>cold-dm</strong> · <strong>followup</strong> · <strong>personalization</strong> · <strong>sequence-builder</strong>. Each reads the full dossier and Merit Code before generating a single word.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-inside-card">
            <p class="mt-inside-card-label">The Humanizer</p>
            <p class="mt-inside-card-p">Always on. Ten-point rewrite. Rhythm, hedges, passive voice, CTAs, research integration. Runs on every output. Every time.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-inside-skills">
        <h3 class="mt-inside-subhead">All 10 output skills</h3>
        <div class="mt-inside-skills-grid">
          <div class="mt-inside-skill">
            <p class="mt-inside-skill-name">Cold Email</p>
            <p class="mt-inside-skill-p">Full 4-email sequence. Research-led opener. New dossier signal each touch. Value add at touch 3. Clean breakup at touch 4. Subject line variants for A/B testing.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-inside-skill">
            <p class="mt-inside-skill-name">Cold DM</p>
            <p class="mt-inside-skill-p">Platform-native for LinkedIn, X, Instagram, TikTok. Each channel gets its own message — different tone, structure, and CTA. Not a copy-paste with paragraphs removed.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-inside-skill">
            <p class="mt-inside-skill-name">Sequence Builder</p>
            <p class="mt-inside-skill-p">Full 5-touch multi-channel sequence from scratch. All touches written. Humanizer runs on each. Logged to the pipeline automatically.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-inside-skill">
            <p class="mt-inside-skill-name">Angle Generator</p>
            <p class="mt-inside-skill-p">10 research-grounded angles per campaign. Trigger-led, insight, contrast, counterintuitive, story, direct. Varied hooks. Humanized openers. Performance-ranked over time.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-inside-skill">
            <p class="mt-inside-skill-name">Follow-Up</p>
            <p class="mt-inside-skill-p">Touches 2–6 with escalation logic. Each uses a new dossier signal not yet referenced. CTA shortens each time. Touch 6 is a breakup that gets replies.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-inside-skill">
            <p class="mt-inside-skill-name">Personalization</p>
            <p class="mt-inside-skill-p">Rewrites any staged message with real dossier signals, layered by signal strength. Checks outbox history — never repeats a detail already used.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-inside-skill">
            <p class="mt-inside-skill-name">Subject Lines</p>
            <p class="mt-inside-skill-p">10 variants per angle. Curiosity, direct, trigger reference, counterintuitive, honest. A/B test pair recommended with one-line rationale.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-inside-skill">
            <p class="mt-inside-skill-name">Weekly Reporter</p>
            <p class="mt-inside-skill-p">Every Monday: sends, reply rates by angle and channel, what to kill, what to scale, what to test next. Updates metrics automatically. Three priorities for the week.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-inside-skill">
            <p class="mt-inside-skill-name">ICP Builder</p>
            <p class="mt-inside-skill-p">10-question deep-dive into the ideal customer. Rewrites <strong>icp.md</strong> completely when targeting drifts or a new segment opens.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-inside-skill">
            <p class="mt-inside-skill-name">Intake</p>
            <p class="mt-inside-skill-p">Builds all 8 Merit Code memory files in a single Q&A session. About 20 minutes. 10 angles generated on completion. The foundation for everything else.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════
       MERIT CODE — The memory system
       ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="mt-section mt-section--deep">
    <div class="section-label">
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
      <div class="label-text">§ 05 — The memory system</div>
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-code">
      <h2 class="mt-code-h">
        8 files per client.<br />
        <em>The whole system recalibrates when you update one.</em>
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-code-deck">
        Merit Code is a set of living markdown files that sit in each client's folder. Every skill reads them before running. You fill them in once during intake. Update one when things change and every subsequent message reflects the new truth.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-code-grid">
        <div class="mt-code-col">
          <p class="mt-code-col-label">Identity Layer</p>
          <div class="mt-code-file">
            <p class="mt-code-file-name">soul.md</p>
            <p class="mt-code-file-p">The belief system. Why this client's work matters. Why the outreach deserves to be read. Read before everything, every session.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-code-file">
            <p class="mt-code-file-name">brand.md</p>
            <p class="mt-code-file-p">Who the client is, what they built, proof points, competitive positioning. The foundation of every proof point used in outreach.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-code-file">
            <p class="mt-code-file-name">voice.md</p>
            <p class="mt-code-file-p">How the client sounds. Tone, banned phrases, how the voice shifts per platform. The humanizer calibrates against this file.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-code-file">
            <p class="mt-code-file-name">offer.md</p>
            <p class="mt-code-file-p">The transformation being sold — not the product, the outcome. The ask. The objections and the honest answers to each.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-code-col">
          <p class="mt-code-col-label">Targeting Layer</p>
          <div class="mt-code-file">
            <p class="mt-code-file-name">icp.md</p>
            <p class="mt-code-file-p">The exact human being being targeted. What they care about. What's blocking them. Where they spend time. Trigger events. Disqualifiers.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-code-file">
            <p class="mt-code-file-name">angles.md</p>
            <p class="mt-code-file-p">10+ outreach hooks ranked by reply rate. Active, paused, or killed based on performance. Retired by the reporter automatically.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-code-file">
            <p class="mt-code-file-name">sequences.md</p>
            <p class="mt-code-file-p">Every active campaign: segment, offer, angle, channel stack, cadence, enrollment count, performance data.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-code-file">
            <p class="mt-code-file-name">metrics.md</p>
            <p class="mt-code-file-p">Reply rates, meeting rates, deals closed. What's working. What to double. What to kill. Updated every Monday by the reporter.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════
       FOR AGENCIES — Multi-client setup
       ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="mt-section mt-section--warm">
    <div class="section-label">
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
      <div class="label-text">§ 06 — Multi-client setup</div>
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-agency">
      <h2 class="mt-agency-h">
        One framework.<br />
        <em>Every client gets their own system.</em>
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-agency-lede">
        Merit is built for agencies running multiple clients at once. Each client lives in their own folder with their own Merit Code files — their own brand, voice, offer, ICP, angles, and pipeline. The skills are shared infrastructure. The memory is completely isolated per client.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-agency-tree">
        <pre class="mt-tree-code"><code><span class="mt-tree-comment"># One clone. Every client isolated.</span>
agency/
├── client-acme/
│   ├── merit-code/     <span class="mt-tree-dim">Acme's memory</span>
│   ├── contacts.json
│   ├── outbox.json
│   └── logfile.txt
├── client-globex/
│   ├── merit-code/     <span class="mt-tree-dim">Globex's memory</span>
│   ├── contacts.json
│   ├── outbox.json
│   └── logfile.txt
└── skills/             <span class="mt-tree-dim">shared across all clients</span></code></pre>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-agency-p">Switch clients by switching folders. No dashboard. No context-switching tax. No risk of one client's voice bleeding into another's messages.</p>
      <p class="mt-agency-p">The ramp-up cost for a new client is one intake session — about 20 minutes. After that, every skill is live and every message is specific to them.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════
       OPEN SOURCE
       ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="mt-section mt-section--centered">
    <div class="section-label">
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
      <div class="label-text">§ 07 — Open source</div>
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-oss">
      <h2 class="mt-oss-h">
        Fork it. Make it yours.<br />
        <em>The framework is yours the moment you clone it.</em>
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-oss-lede">
        Merit is MIT licensed. Every file is readable, editable, and forkable. Add skills for your agency's workflow. Change the Merit Code schema to match your niche. Build your own chain. The framework is a starting point, not a ceiling.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-oss-cta">
        <a class="btn-primary" href="https://github.com/701am/Merit">
          Clone on GitHub
          <span class="btn-icon" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-oss-license">
        MIT License · 33 files · Runs in Claude Code or OpenCode
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════
       GET STARTED — Install
       ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="mt-section mt-section--warm">
    <div class="section-label">
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
      <div class="label-text">§ 08 — Setup</div>
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-install">
      <h2 class="mt-install-h">
        Clone it.<br />
        Run intake.<br />
        <em>Send your first message.</em>
      </h2>

      <ol class="mt-install-steps">
        <li>
          <span class="mt-install-num">1</span>
          <div class="mt-install-body">
            <h4>Clone and open</h4>
            <p>Clone the repo and open it in Claude Code or OpenCode. Claude Code reads <strong>CLAUDE.md</strong> automatically. OpenCode reads <strong>AGENTS.md</strong>. Both contain the same operating instructions — pick your runtime.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="mt-install-num">2</span>
          <div class="mt-install-body">
            <h4>Run intake for your first client</h4>
            <p>Merit asks the questions that populate all 8 Merit Code files. Brand, voice, offer, ICP, and 10 angles generated on completion. About 20 minutes. Makes every subsequent message significantly better.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="mt-install-num">3</span>
          <div class="mt-install-body">
            <h4>Add a prospect and write</h4>
            <p>Add a contact. Run <strong>cold-email</strong> or <strong>cold-dm</strong>. Merit checks for a Research Dossier — if one doesn't exist, researcher runs first. Then the skill writes. Then humanizer rewrites. The sequence stages in <strong>outbox.json</strong> waiting for your approval. Nothing sends without a human sign-off.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <div class="mt-install-terminal">
        <pre class="mt-term"><code>$ git clone github.com/701am/Merit
$ cd Merit

<span class="mt-term-prompt">Run intake</span>
Merit: Let's build your Merit Code.
      What's the client's company name?

<span class="mt-term-dim">// ~20 min later: all 8 files populated</span>

<span class="mt-term-prompt">Run cold-email</span>
Merit: Who is this for?
Researching... Writing... Humanizing...
<span class="mt-term-success">✓ 4-email sequence staged in outbox.json</span></code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-install-cta">
        <a class="btn-primary" href="https://github.com/701am/Merit">
          Clone on GitHub — Free
          <span class="btn-icon" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════
       CONVICTION
       ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="mt-section mt-section--deep">
    <div class="mt-conviction">
      <h2 class="mt-conviction-h">
        Your clients' offers<br />
        <em>deserve to be heard.</em>
      </h2>

      <div class="mt-conviction-body">
        <p>Most cold outreach fails not because the offer is wrong — but because the message never earns the right to deliver it. The prospect deletes before the second line. The reply never comes. The offer never lands.</p>
        <p>Merit exists for the agencies that refuse to accept that. The ones who know their clients' work is worth a real conversation — and who want a system that produces outreach good enough to start one.</p>
        <p>Research-led. Humanized. Specific enough that no one else could have sent it. <em>That's the standard. Merit is the system for reaching it, consistently, across every client, every campaign, every message.</em></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════
       CONTRIBUTE
       ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="mt-section mt-section--centered">
    <div class="section-label">
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
      <div class="label-text">§ 09 — Contribute</div>
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-contribute">
      <h2 class="mt-contribute-h">
        Built by one.<br />
        <em>Better with many.</em>
      </h2>

      <div class="mt-contribute-grid">
        <div class="mt-contribute-card">
          <p class="mt-contribute-card-label">Add a skill</p>
          <p class="mt-contribute-card-p">Build a new .md file following the skill format and open a PR. If it respects the chain — researcher → skill → humanizer — it belongs here.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-contribute-card">
          <p class="mt-contribute-card-label">File an issue</p>
          <p class="mt-contribute-card-p">Weak output, a missing dossier field, a humanizer rule that should exist. Open an issue. Be specific. Here as everywhere, specificity is the point.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-contribute-card">
          <p class="mt-contribute-card-label">Fork and adapt</p>
          <p class="mt-contribute-card-p">Rename it. Adjust the Merit Code schema for your niche. Add memory files your clients need. You don't need permission. That's the whole point.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════
       FINAL CTA
       ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="mt-section mt-section--coda">
    <div class="mt-coda">
      <h2 class="mt-coda-h">
        Make something wonderful<br />
